toppage during the bullet extraction process.\n    * Trigger is soft, but fire takes place when the trigger is pulled fully back.\n    * Slow hitting firing pin\n\nI would add here is that i returned Taurus PT709 Slim after three days of its purchase in September 2010 with a instant loss of 3K.[/quote]\n\nDear Sir, Thanks for guidance.\n\nMajor disadventage I think is "   * Slide was encountering the stoppage during the bullet extraction process" this is real problem as you experienced, for other concerns I think plastic seems to break/wear & tear etc but my G2 surefire tourch is of a plastic that is more tougher than steel, other examples are of Glock etc, whatever now I am inclined towards RAMI as can not depend my life on whatever you explained in such detail. Thanks again.', 0, 1, '119.154.88.108', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 6314, 175597),
